\centering
\includegraphics[scale=0.7]{Scompare.eps}%"scale" КѓЕФЪ§зжЮЊЭМаЮЕФПэЖШЃЌвВПЩгУ"width=1.0\columnwidth" ЖЈвх
\caption{(Color online) Comparison of the present $S_{17}(0)$ factor with the previous results. The direct measurements are performed by Filippone et al. \cite{fil83l}, Hammache et al. \cite{hamm98}, Baby et al. \cite{bab03l}, and Junghans et al. \cite{jun10}. The transfer reaction was carried out by Liu et al. \cite{wpliu96}, Azhari et al. \cite{azh06} and Das et al. \cite{das06}. Ogata et al. \cite{oga03} reanalyzed the transfer reaction data from Ref. \cite{wpliu96} and renewed the $S_{17}(0)$ factor. The Coulomb dissociation experiments are performed by Motobayashi et al. \cite{moto94}, Iwasa et al. \cite{iwa99}, Sch\"{u}mann et al. \cite{sch03}. The work via charge symmetry method includes the $^{13}$C($^7$Li,\,$^8$Li)$^{12}$C reaction by Trache et al. \cite{tra03}, the $^7$Li($^8$Li,\,$^7$Li)$^8$Li reaction by Howell et al. \cite{howe13}, and the $^7$Li(d,\,p)$^8$Li reaction in the present work (the red star). The light grey and the dark grey shadows represent the recommended values by Adelberger et al. (1998) \cite{eri98} and by Adelberger et al. (2011) \cite{ade11}, respectively.}
\label{fig:figure4}
\end{figure}

The astrophysical $^7$Be(p,\,$\gamma$)$^8$B reaction rates for
the direct capture and the broad $3^+$ resonance can be calculated with
\begin{equation}\label{eq9}
\begin{aligned}
N_A<\sigma \upsilon> _{nr} =&N_A(\frac{8}{\pi\mu})^{1/2}\frac{1}{(kT)^{3/2}}\\
&\times\int_0^\infty S(E)\exp[-(\frac{E_G}{E})^{1/2}-\frac{E}{kT}]\textrm{d}E ,
\end{aligned}
\end{equation}
where $N_A$ is Avogadro's number. For the narrow $1^+$ resonance, the reaction rate can be approximated by
\begin{eqnarray}
\label{eq10}%
N_A \langle\sigma v\rangle_{res} = N_A \big({2\pi \over \mu kT}
\big)^{3/2}\hbar^2\omega\gamma\exp(-E_R/kT),
\end{eqnarray}
where the resonance strength $\omega\gamma$ is given by
\begin{eqnarray}
\label{eq11} \omega\gamma={2J+1 \over
(2J_{1}+1)(2J_{2}+1)}{\Gamma_{p}(E_R)\Gamma_{\gamma}(E_R) \over
\Gamma_{\textrm{tot}}},
\end{eqnarray}
The present reaction rates of the direct capture and the $1^+$ and $3^+$ resonances and total reaction rates are listed in Table \ref{tab:table3}. The direct capture dominates the $^7$Be(p,\,$\gamma$)$^8$B reaction in the whole temperature range of $T_9$ = 0.003-10, especially at temperatures of $T_9 \leq 0.5$ the direct component accounts for more than 99.5\%.

In Figure~\ref{fig:figure5} we compare the present rate with the previous compilations of REACLIB~\cite{reaclib}, NACRE~\cite{nacre1} and NACRE II~\cite{nacre2}. The present rate is about 20\% slower than the REACLIB rate, while it is in good agreement with the NACRE and the NACRE II rates.

